'''健康食品癡迷症'''（{{lang-en|orthorexia nervosa，又稱orthorexia}}）是美國醫生 Steven Bratman 於1997年時提出的概念，指人們因過度追求[[健康飲食|健康飲食]]而表現出極端的[[飲食失調|飲食失調]]，症狀包括身心焦慮、無法以一種不經計劃的方式進食、除了飲食之外對其它有利於健康的活動失去興趣等，極端情況下會使人處於嚴重[[營養不良|營養不良]]狀態，甚至導致死亡<ref name="Healthy food obsession sparks rise in new eating disorder">{{cite news | url        = http://www.guardian.co.uk/society/2009/aug/16/orthorexia-mental-health-eating-disorder | title        = Healthy food obsession sparks rise in new eating disorder | first        = Amelia | last        = Hill | date        = 16 August 2009 | work        = The Guardian | accessdate        = 16 October 2010 | location        = London | archive-date        = 2013-06-23 | archive-url        = https://web.archive.org/web/20130623032434/http://www.guardian.co.uk/society/2009/aug/16/orthorexia-mental-health-eating-disorder | dead-url        = no }}</ref><ref>Bratman, Steven (2014) http://www.orthorexia.com/what-is-orthorexia/ {{Wayback|url=http://www.orthorexia.com/what-is-orthorexia/ |date=20201202123651 }}. Accessed 1/1/2016</ref><ref>{{cite news | url       = http://www.time.com/time/health/article/0,8599,1963297,00.html | title       = Orthorexia: Can Healthy Eating Be a Disorder? | first       = Bonnie | last       = Rochman | date       = 12 February 2010 | accessdate       = 4 January 2012 | work       = Time | archive-date       = 2012-10-31 | archive-url       = https://www.webcitation.org/6BolHeR9R?url=http://www.time.com/time/health/article/0,8599,1963297,00.html | dead-url       = no }}</ref>。

Ursula Philpot是{{le|英国饮食协会|British Dietetic Association}}的[[會長|會長]]，也是[[利茲貝克特大學|利茲貝克特大學]]的{{le|高级讲师|senior lecturer}}<ref>{{cite web
 | url        = http://www.channel4.com/programmes/supersize-vs-superskinny/articles/ursula-philpot
 | title        = Supersize vs Superskinny - Expert Profiles - Ursula Philpot
 | date        = 2011-04-07
 | work        = Channel 4
 | accessdate        = 2010-10-19
 | archive-date        = 2013-01-28
 | archive-url        = https://web.archive.org/web/20130128001913/http://www.channel4.com/programmes/supersize-vs-superskinny/articles/ursula-philpot
 | dead-url        = no
 }}</ref>，他在2009年時在《[[衛報|衛報]]》描述健康食品痴迷症是：「只在意他們所吃食物的品質，而且依照他們自身認為哪一種食物「天然健康」，而限制其本身的飲食。」，這和[[神经性厌食症|神经性厌食症]]及[[神經性暴食症|神經性暴食症]]等[[进食障碍|进食障碍]]不同，後者主要是針對其進食的量<ref name="Healthy food obsession sparks rise in new eating disorder"/>。

2013年時，[[美國精神醫學學會|美國精神醫學學會]]（APA）尚未將健康食品癡迷症視為是飲食失調<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://rua.ua.es/dspace/bitstream/10045/34900/1/jhse_Vol_8_N_IV_1045-1053.pdf |title=Exploring scientific legitimacy of orthorexia nervosa:a newly emerging eating disorder |accessdate=2016-10-03 |archive-date=2019-03-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190307223551/https://rua.ua.es/dspace/bitstream/10045/34900/1/jhse_Vol_8_N_IV_1045-1053.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>，而廣為使用的《[[精神疾病診斷與統計手冊|精神疾病診斷與統計手冊]]》（DSM）及其他權威性的來源也還沒將此症狀列在其正式診斷中{{Ref_label|A|a|none}}。

